---
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import MainLayout from "@/layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="No Privacy Policy | YOLO License" description="YOLOVibeCodeBootCamp Radical Transparency Statement and No Rights Reserved Approach">
  <Container>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-700 to-cyan-500">
        NO PRIVACY POLICY
      </h1>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-10">
        Our radical openness approach: No Privacy Policy, No Rights Reserved
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-200 via-pink-100 to-indigo-200 dark:from-purple-800/60 dark:via-pink-800/50 dark:to-indigo-800/60 p-8 rounded-2xl mb-10 border border-purple-300/50 dark:border-purple-500/30 shadow-lg backdrop-blur-sm">
        <p class="text-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-800 via-pink-700 to-indigo-800 dark:from-purple-100 dark:via-pink-100 dark:to-indigo-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent font-bold leading-relaxed">
          In a world where AI is reshaping everything, we choose radical openness over secrecy. No privacy policy, no rights reserved - just pure YOLO energy.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Traditional privacy policies and copyright restrictions are walls to keep people out. That's not our style. At YOLOVibeCodeBootCamp, 
          we're breaking down barriers with radical openness - because when more people have access to powerful tools 
          and knowledge, we all benefit. We don't just have a minimal privacy policy - we have NO privacy policy.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          We believe technology should empower everyone, not just a privileged few. As AI reshapes our economy and job market, 
          the answer isn't to hoard knowledge but to share it widely, helping people discover new forms of value and 
          creativity within themselves.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-200 via-blue-100 to-purple-200 dark:from-cyan-800/60 dark:via-blue-800/50 dark:to-purple-800/60 p-8 rounded-2xl my-8 border border-cyan-300/50 dark:border-cyan-500/30 shadow-lg backdrop-blur-sm">
          <p class="font-bold text-2xl mb-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-800 via-pink-700 to-indigo-800 dark:from-purple-100 dark:via-pink-100 dark:to-indigo-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent" 
             style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #7c2d92, #be185d, #3730a3) !important; -webkit-background-clip: text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent !important; background-clip: text !important; color: transparent !important;">YOLO LICENSE - NO RIGHTS RESERVED:</p>
          <p class="font-semibold leading-relaxed text-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-800 via-pink-700 to-indigo-800 dark:from-purple-100 dark:via-pink-100 dark:to-indigo-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
             style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #7c2d92, #be185d, #3730a3) !important; -webkit-background-clip: text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent !important; background-clip: text !important; color: transparent !important;">
            We've released all our content under our own YOLO License - no rights reserved. Copy it, modify it, sell it - we don't care. 
            Take our materials, our explanations, our code, our designs - everything - and spread them freely. 
            That's not piracy - it's exactly what we want you to do. The value is in spreading the idea, not restricting it.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <p>
          The more people who understand how to use these tools effectively, the more creative fires we can light. 
          So instead of telling you what we're keeping secret, here's exactly what we're doing with the little bit 
          of info we collect from you.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">The Stuff That Drives Us</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">Here's what we're all about:</p>
        
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-purple-400 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1">1</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-lg dark:text-white">Share More, Get More</strong><span class="dark:text-slate-200"> - When everyone shares what they know, everyone learns faster</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-blue-500 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1">2</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-lg dark:text-white">No Hidden Stuff</strong><span class="dark:text-slate-200"> - We just tell you what's up. It's simpler that way</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-cyan-500 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1">3</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-lg dark:text-white">Credit Where It's Due</strong><span class="dark:text-slate-200"> - We'll say where ideas came from rather than pretending we invented everything</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-500 to-teal-500 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1">4</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-lg dark:text-white">Ripple Effects</strong><span class="dark:text-slate-200"> - We want what we teach to spread and help as many people as possible</span>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">Stuff We Need From You</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">We keep it simple - just the basics:</p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 dark:text-slate-200">
          <li>Your name and email so we know who's coming to our workshops</li>
          <li>Payment details (Stripe handles this, not us)</li>
          <li>Anonymous site visit info to see what's working</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">What We Do With It</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">Pretty straightforward stuff:</p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 dark:text-slate-200">
          <li>Send you workshop confirmation and prep materials</li>
          <li>Let you know about new workshops (but not spam you)</li>
          <li>Improve our materials based on what people find most helpful</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">Security (The Boring But Important Bit)</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">
          We take the basic security steps you'd expect - SSL encryption, decent passwords, 
          that kind of thing. We're not storing state secrets here, but we're not careless either.
          However, in the spirit of radical transparency, we want to be clear: we prioritize openness over privacy.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">Our YOLO License</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">
          We've created our own YOLO License - a public domain dedication with no rights reserved. You can find the full text in our 
          <a href="https://github.com/rvegajr/yolovibe-website/blob/main/LICENSE" class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-300 hover:underline">GitHub repository</a>.
          The essence is simple: take our work, use it however you want, no attribution required (though appreciated).
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 dark:text-white">Questions?</h2>
        
        <p class="dark:text-slate-200">
          Just email us at <a href="mailto:contact@yolovibecodebootcamps.com" class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-300 hover:underline">contact@yolovibecodebootcamps.com</a> - we're real humans and we'll 
          actually respond. No automated nonsense.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-300 via-pink-200 to-indigo-300 dark:from-purple-700/70 dark:via-pink-700/60 dark:to-indigo-700/70 p-10 rounded-2xl mt-10 text-center border border-purple-400/40 dark:border-purple-400/30 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-sm">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-900 via-pink-800 to-indigo-900 dark:from-purple-100 dark:via-pink-100 dark:to-indigo-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-6 leading-tight"
             style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #581c87, #be185d, #3730a3) !important; 
                    -webkit-background-clip: text !important; 
                    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent !important; 
                    background-clip: text !important; 
                    color: transparent !important;
                    -webkit-text-stroke: 2px transparent !important;
                    text-shadow: 
                      0 0 0 2px #7c3aed,
                      0 0 0 4px #ec4899,
                      0 0 0 6px #4f46e5,
                      0 0 20px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.5),
                      0 0 30px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.3),
                      0 0 40px rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.2) !important;">
            Want to join our mission of radical openness?
          </p>
          <a href="/#book" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-pink-600 hover:from-purple-700 hover:to-pink-700 text-white font-bold py-4 px-8 rounded-xl transition-all transform hover:scale-105 shadow-lg">
            Book a Workshop
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</MainLayout>
